      "content": "\"In computer science and information science, an ontology is a formal naming and definition of the t ypes, properties, and interrelationships of the entities that really exist in a particular domain of discourse.\"\n\n\na subject first thuroughly explored by metaphysicians in the 1600 and brought into computer science by Tom Gruber in 1993, remains one of the most bedeviling and difficult projects in the quest for human knowledge. I would argue that Google and Facebook's success are based not on some engineering feat, but in a clear structure and accessibility to their data.\n\nThe fundamental question of research is how to aquire the information, and how to translate that information into a searchable, sortable, understandable and useable structure.",
